rComments: loved the prof! he made the lectures really interesting and was always available to help out with the material
Dr. Lapointe was a great teacher. He is very competent and patient as well as helpful. Even though the class was very condensed he made it enjoyable and possible to get through it.

I have so many good things to say about Dr. Lapointe. He was a great prof in terms of material delivery, clear grading criteria, and always available outside of class and office hours to answer any questions. I will go out of my way to take one of his classes again. Seriously just a class act. Best professor I have ever had.

An amazing professor. He made me enjoy learning again.  He's incredibly nice and sweet, he cares a lot about all of his students, and loves discussion and exploring every idea presented. Really my ideal professor. His grading is generous as long as you put in the effort.

Fantastic cross section of lit to really sink your teeth into. He also makes sure every student is engaged and  welcomes all thoughts and ideas. Has a horrible relationship with his AV station, which provides endless entertainment....I'm hoping to take another course of his next fall.
Great Great Great. Thank you Dr. Lapointe for all the great classes! One of the best profs at UofT where you actually learn and not just marinate in a class. Love him.

Dr. Lapointe's course in Canadian history was amazing! He really cares about his students and tries to push their critical thinking skills far. Every now and then the class goes off on a tangent, but, oh, what a fascinating tangent. Dr. Lapointe has a great sense of humor and is very approachable.

What a wonderful class and excellent professor! Dr. Lapointe changed my life: I never thought I was "smart" enough to go to university and thought my writing abilities were poor, but Michael proved me wrong on both accounts. Thank you, sir!
Dr. Lapointe is a great teacher. Very approachable and clear. Nobody is left out, unlike in 2nd year where profs are paycheck zombies. Thanks for everything Michael!

A superb teacher! Very knowledgeable, passionate about literature, especially anything dealing with Ireland. Tries hard to teach using different methods. Lapointe is keen on students learning to think critically.

One of the most memorable teachers.  He cared about his students, kept interest in the class and not only covered english literature but provided a wealth of information regarding the authors.  Excellent teacher!!  Would highly recommend!!

really good teacher, straightforward and to the point. Enthusiastic about teaching the history of contemporary Canada (academic bridging!). Heavy course, many novels, many assignments. Fair marker. Mostly cheery disposition.

i entered this bridging course in canadian history as a necessary evil on the road to admission to the faculty of arts and sciences as a mature student - dr lapointe imbued me with a passion for this topic, such that i am pondering changing my academic direction

Dr. Lapointe was funny, approachable, and made evident and considerable efforts to engage his students and make the material presented interesting and exciting. He offered sincere encouragement and made himself available to provide extra assistance as needed. He was always prompt in responding to emails.

Dr. Lapointe kept the material interesting and relevant. Lectures were interesting, and in-class group presentations and debates made class engaging and a pleasure to attend. Dr. Lapointe wants his students to do well, and supports them throughout the year. Contemporary Canada, 1 in-class test, 1 mid-term and final exam.
Not bad. Funny and approachable. He tries very hard to do a good job, and if you bump into him outside class he'll recognize you and chat with you. Nice guy.
Very unclear!  He does not offer much help to his students and can be very emotional at times.  One of the not-so-good course at UofT.
